modules.description: This component provides operations to build and manage hierarchical service directories for HTTP routing, supporting dynamic path registration with curried arguments and Lwt-based asynchronous handlers. It works with nested path patterns and service trees to enable use cases like merging directory subtrees, prefixing routes, or dynamically generating endpoints based on request paths. Key capabilities include method-specific routing, path-based service lookup, and composing complex server behaviors from modular directory fragments.
